Subject: [PATCH] From peterz@infradead.org Thu May 15 09:55:55 2008 Date: Fri, 04 Apr 2008 17:42:53 +0200 To: Steven Rostedt <rostedt@goodmis.org>, Clark Williams <williams@redhat.com> Cc: linux-rt-users <linux-rt-users@vger.kernel.org>, linux-kernel <linux-kernel@vger.kernel.org> Subject: [PATCH -rt] shorten softirq kernel thread names Subject: -rt: shorten softirq kernel thread names

Shorten the softirq kernel thread names because they often overflow
the limited comm length.

Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra <a.p.zijlstra@chello.nl>
---
 kernel/softirq.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/kernel/softirq.c b/kernel/softirq.c
index 361ec89..1f09455 100644
--- a/kernel/softirq.c
+++ b/kernel/softirq.c
@@ -805,7 +805,7 @@ static int __cpuinit cpu_callback(struct notifier_block *nfb,
 		for (i = 0; i < MAX_SOFTIRQ; i++) {
 			p = kthread_create(ksoftirqd,
 					   &per_cpu(ksoftirqd, hotcpu)[i],
-					   "softirq-%s/%d", softirq_names[i],
+					   "sirq-%s/%d", softirq_names[i],
 					   hotcpu);
 			if (IS_ERR(p)) {
 				printk("ksoftirqd %d for %i failed\n", i,
